{"TopicId":161465,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Far From Home: Single Engine","CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T15:18:40Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T15:18:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EA recent trade embargo has caused a surge in prices for engine components. As a result, the Kerbal Space Program management has created a new rule: vehicles may use no more than a single engine, and it must be recovered intact.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour goal is to get at least one Kerbal as far from home as possible, and return, on a single stock engine. This single engine must be your only means of propulsion. No \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E or refueling is permitted (since any single-engine \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E would then have an infinite score). No decoupler launching, cheats, infinite fuel, or anything gimmicky.\u00A0Staging is fine; you can use drop tanks as desired. You only have to recover the Kerbal and the engine, and you can do so separately if desired. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E can be used as long as it produces no prograde acceleration at any point (e.g., it can be used for attitude control and deorbiting but not for anything prograde).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter several entries, there will be one leaderboard organized into three levels: Atmospheric, Orbital, and Escape. In Atmospheric, your score is total distance traveled; in Orbital, your score is your apoapsis (with periapse over 70 km); in Escape, your score is your velocity at the edge of Kerbin\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E. For all levels, you get a 150% multiplier for each additional Kerbal; for the latter two levels, you get a 2x multiplier for each world you land on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003ELEADERBOARD\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ELevel 3: Escape\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97346-jouni/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002297346\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97346-jouni/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Jouni\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(escape velocity unknown)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/178370-zeta-function/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022178370\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/178370-zeta-function/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@zeta function\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(honorable mention; burned up on re-entry)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ELevel 2: Orbital\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/177969-dman0829/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022177969\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/177969-dman0829/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dman0829\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(83,553 km * 1.5^14 = 24,391,566 km)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/142082-aetharan/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022142082\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/142082-aetharan/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Aetharan\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(83,555 km)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nsevenperforce (256\u00A0km * 1.5^1 = 384 km)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ELevel 3: Atmospheric\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\n(no entries yet)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-03T12:46:33Z\u0022 title=\u002206/03/2017 12:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by sevenperforce\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T15:58:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuestion: Does Solid rocket boosters (of all size, including the Sepraton and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Launch Escape System\u0022\u003ELES\u003C/abbr\u003E) count as an engine or not?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T16:09:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223077618\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496419083\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165777\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jestersage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Jestersage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuestion: Does Solid rocket boosters (of all size, including the Sepraton and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Launch Escape System\u0022\u003ELES\u003C/abbr\u003E) count as an engine or not?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. If it pushes the craft in a prograde direction, it\u0027s an engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can use sepratrons to help with stage separation if you want, as long as they don\u0027t produce prograde acceleration on the main vehicle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will edit the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E to note that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters are fine as long as they aren\u0027t used for prograde acceleration at any time. They can be used for retrograde acceleration (e.g., deorbit burns).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"icantmakemodels","CreatedById":90378,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T16:43:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHold my beer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/161525-wip-hold-my-beer-one-engine-infinite-range/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-03T16:35:43Z\u0022 title=\u002206/03/2017 04:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by icantmakemodels\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EProgress report #2\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T17:49:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223077679\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496421806\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290378\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022icantmakemodels\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n55 minutes ago, icantmakemodels said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEDIT:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Am I allowed to use multiple engines as long as they\u0027re all together? e.g., a cluster of six \u0022Vector\u0022 Engines\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEDIT2:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Are we allowed sepratrons, as long as they\u0027re for seperating?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, you cannot cluster engines. You can only use one engine, and it must be stock.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs I stated above, sepratrons and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters are fine as long as they aren\u0027t used to thrust prograde. They can be used to thrust retrograde for your final deorbit burn if needed (for example, if you\u0027ve jettisoned your engine for independent re-entry and you need to deorbit your capsule).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"icantmakemodels","CreatedById":90378,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T18:00:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about recovering the engine and re-launching it? Or do I have to make a re-fueling rig?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman0829","CreatedById":177969,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T18:03:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nApogee 83,553,434(could exit kerbins \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003Esoi\u003C/abbr\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n15 Kerbals\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nS3-KS 25x4 \u0022mammoth\u0022 liquid fuel engine\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nScore 2,506,603,000\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nVideo Evidence Coming\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-02T20:10:06Z\u0022 title=\u002206/02/2017 08:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Dman0829\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T18:06:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223077775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496426401\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290378\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022icantmakemodels\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, icantmakemodels said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about recovering the engine and re-launching it? Or do I have to make a re-fueling rig?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E or fuel transfer. One launch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"icantmakemodels","CreatedById":90378,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T19:13:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo as long as I launch the fuel, the refit rig, and everything else all at once, I\u0027m good?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T19:27:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223077881\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496430834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290378\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022icantmakemodels\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, icantmakemodels said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo as long as I launch the fuel, the refit rig, and everything else all at once, I\u0027m good?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a single engine, sure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zeta function","CreatedById":178370,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T20:51:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you escape kerbin, how is it scored?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T21:19:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223078013\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496436692\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022178370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022zeta function\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, zeta function said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you escape kerbin, how is it scored?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHighest velocity at escape, I suppose. But remember that you\u0027ve got to actually return to Kerbin, so....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s my entry, just for fun. Obviously this could be way better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/a/TuU01\u0022 style=\u0022height:453px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n256 kilometers!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zeta function","CreatedById":178370,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T21:59:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223078051\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496438379\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n39 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHighest velocity at escape, I suppose. But remember that you\u0027ve got to actually return to Kerbin, so....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/a/TuU01\u0022 style=\u0022height:453px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif it is measured by highest velocity at escape, then Dman\u0027s score would drop a lot if he decided to escape instead, the only thing I can think of this moment is distance from kerbins orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut that would be a large gain for a little velocity change.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-02T22:00:37Z\u0022 title=\u002206/02/2017 10:00  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by zeta function\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ENot a very sound scoring system.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zeta function","CreatedById":178370,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T22:39:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI managed to get past duna, but then i burned up in re-entry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ManEatingApe","CreatedById":151354,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T22:46:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157695-sevenperforce/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022157695\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157695-sevenperforce/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sevenperforce\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Is a dual mode engine like the RAPIER ok?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223078051\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496438379\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHighest velocity at escape, I suppose. But remember that you\u0027ve got to actually return to Kerbin, so....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor crafts\u00A0that manage to escape Kerbin you could have a separate leaderboard with AP above Kerbol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jouni","CreatedById":97346,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T22:55:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is not a real entry, just a proof-of-concept.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNever underestimate the power of the Twin-Boar. With a couple of drop tanks, a Twin-Boar can give the single-kerbal capsule and some other payload over 6500 m/s of delta-v. After a bit too steep ascent, I had around 3250 m/s left at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022silly_thing_1.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://jltsiren.kapsi.fi/ksp/1.3/silly_thing_1.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbin\u0027s orbital period is 1 year. If you launch into interplanetary space with an integral number of years as the orbital period, you will encounter Kerbin after a single orbit. I chose an easy orbit, where the encounter is at the periapsis and the apoapsis is 1 year after the launch. This required a bit over 1280 m/s for the launch, and around 2 m/s for fine-tuning the encounter at the apoapsis.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was left with almost 2000 m/s for managing the reentry and landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022silly_thing_2.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://jltsiren.kapsi.fi/ksp/1.3/silly_thing_2.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was necessary, as there is a lot of dry mass for the cross-section. On the other hand, because the Twin-Boar has a high impact tolerance, you don\u0027t have to carry enough parachutes for a safe landing. Especially if you manage to hit the ocean.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022silly_thing_3.jpeg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://jltsiren.kapsi.fi/ksp/1.3/silly_thing_3.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T23:02:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223078104\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496440767\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022178370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022zeta function\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, zeta function said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif it is measured by highest velocity at escape, then Dman\u0027s score would drop a lot if he decided to escape instead, the only thing I can think of this moment is distance from kerbins orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut that would be a large gain for a little velocity change.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEscape automatically beats a high-apogee orbit, so increased velocity at escape is a pretty good metric.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223078174\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496444149\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297346\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jouni\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Jouni said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is not a real entry, just a proof-of-concept.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNever underestimate the power of the Twin-Boar. With a couple of drop tanks, a Twin-Boar can give the single-kerbal capsule and some other payload over 6500 m/s of delta-v. After a bit too steep ascent, I had around 3250 m/s left at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow, very nice! Top of the leaderboard, you are.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat was your escape velocity?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI really should come up with a way to add a multiplier or alternate scoring mechanism for landings on other worlds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder what a Twin Boar could do for a horizontal-launch-with-staging, like I used.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-02T23:03:13Z\u0022 title=\u002206/02/2017 11:03  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by sevenperforce\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman0829","CreatedById":177969,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-02T23:59:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo whats the definite scoring for out of kerbins \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003Esoi\u003C/abbr\u003E. In theory any vessel with correct timing could make it to eeloo and return for almost no delta-v with gravity assists and returning much the same. This challenge might need to be redone or with some limitations or instead of including orbits use the total distance in the atmosphere on a single jet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aetharan","CreatedById":142082,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-03T06:24:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, my first \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E to actually, y\u0027know, \u003Cem\u003Eorbit \u003C/em\u003Ehas achieved an AP of\u00A083,554,619m and returned in one piece!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/2Fmhx\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EImgur Album\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\nAnd a suggestion for scoring wildly disparate entries: \u00A0Do three brackets. \u00A01) No orbit? \u00A0Ground distance covered. \u00A02) Kerbin orbit? \u00A0Highest AP. \u00A03) Kerbol orbit? \u00A0Highest AP \u002B\u00A0PE.\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-12-24T04:25:32Z\u0022 title=\u002212/24/2017 04:25  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 24, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Aetharan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EFixing Imgur links.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-03T12:51:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223078161\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496443606\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022151354\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ManEatingApe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, ManEatingApe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157695-sevenperforce/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022157695\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157695-sevenperforce/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sevenperforce\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Is a dual mode engine like the RAPIER ok?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbsolutely. Any stock engine is fine. If you can get something off the ground with an ion engine, more power to you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"icantmakemodels","CreatedById":90378,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-03T15:49:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003EHow about for Kerbin-escape missions, score by Apoapsis above Kerbol --\u00A0the same way the K-Prize does it.\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor scoring: Ditto \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/142082-aetharan/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022142082\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/142082-aetharan/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Aetharan\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n---\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill working on the infinite-range HMB craft. Although I think that the single-launch restriction is pointless since we can only have one engine anyway. How about \u0022Infinite launches as long as you don\u0027re re-launch your single engine.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-03T15:56:11Z\u0022 title=\u002206/03/2017 03:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by icantmakemodels\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-03T16:27:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223078925\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496504954\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290378\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022icantmakemodels\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, icantmakemodels said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill working on the infinite-range HMB craft. Although I think that the single-launch restriction is pointless since we can only have one engine anyway. How about \u0022Infinite launches as long as you don\u0027re re-launch your single engine.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause you want to have the same craft come back and refuel using engineless tankers \u0022launched\u0022 onto the runway? That wouldn\u0027t be allowed, no. That\u0027s why I said no refueling or \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E. The point is to get as far as you can with only the fuel you can lift using a single engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"icantmakemodels","CreatedById":90378,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-03T16:30:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EMy evil plan:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) Launch a tank into orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) Return to the runway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3) Pick up another tank.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4) Repeat from step 1 as necessary\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5) Launch jeb into orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n6) Dock everything together\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n7) Go do a Jool-5 or something\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n8) Return home\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt least make a multi-launch-refueled-still-no-\u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003Eisru\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0leauge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-03T16:31:46Z\u0022 title=\u002206/03/2017 04:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by icantmakemodels\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-03T17:41:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223078962\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161465\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496507439\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290378\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022icantmakemodels\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, icantmakemodels said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EMy evil plan:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) Launch a tank into orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) Return to the runway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3) Pick up another tank.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4) Repeat from step 1 as necessary\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5) Launch jeb into orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n6) Dock everything together\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n7) Go do a Jool-5 or something\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n8) Return home\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt least make a multi-launch-refueled-still-no-\u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003Eisru\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0leauge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, that\u0027s not quite the spirit of the challenge; I said no refueling because I wanted people to use only the fuel they could get off the ground in a single launch. But don\u0027t let that stop you from making it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"icantmakemodels","CreatedById":90378,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-03T17:42:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, make a category for multi-launch-refueled-at-\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E and another for single-launch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProblem solved.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-03T17:42:56Z\u0022 title=\u002206/03/2017 05:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by icantmakemodels\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}